Building Cloud2Sim using source using maven and running an example
-------------------------------------------------------------------
To build using maven:
mvn clean install

skipping the tests:
$ mvn clean install -Dmaven.skip.test=true

To skip executing the tests:
$ mvn clean install -DskipTests


Built distribution inside distribution/target.
--------------------------------------------------
$ tar -xzvf distribution/target/cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz
$ mv cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT/jars/cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT/jars/cloudsim-examples-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT/jars/cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar .


Running the Simulations.
-------------------------
To run an existing example:
$ java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:cloudsim-examples-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/hazelcast-3.2.jar:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.applications.main.statics.Simulator

To initiate an instance without running any specific code:
$ java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/hazelcast-3.2.jar:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.applications.main.dynamics.Initiator


Running Cloud2Sim with Adaptive Scaling.
--------------------------------------------
Initiate the ScalableSimulator from the master node.
$ java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/hazelcast-3.2.jar:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.applications.main.dynamics.ScalableSimulator

Initiate the IntelligentAdaptiveScaler from the other nodes.
$ java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/hazelcast-3.2.jar:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.scale.ias.IntelligentAdaptiveScaler


Running the Map-Reduce Simulations.
-----------------------------------
The workload files are inside the folder conf/mapreduce/
You may replace or add more or bigger load files.

1) Using Hazelcast
------------------
Set the map-reduce workload size in the conf/cloud2sim.properties.
# By default, up to 128 460, by using the 3 default files in conf/mapreduce
mapReduceSize=10

To run the simulations,
$ java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/hazelcast-3.2.jar:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.mapreduce.hazelcast.HzMapReduceSimulator

To run with nohup, printing the output to nohup.out,
$ nohup java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/hazelcast-3.2.jar:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.mapreduce.hazelcast.HzMapReduceSimulator > nohup.out &

2) Using Infinispan
--------------------
Set the map-reduce workload size in the conf/infinispan.properties.
# By default, up to 128 460, by using the 3 default files in conf/mapreduce
mapReduceSize=10

To run the initiator,
$ nohup java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/*:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.infinispan.Initiator > nohup.out &

To run the simulations,
$ nohup java -classpath cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar:lib/*:cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pt.inesc_id.gsd.cloud2sim.mapreduce.infinispan.InfMapReduceSimulator > nohup.out &

Copy the files to the other instances.
----------------------------------------
$ scp -r . pradeeban@146.193.41.145:/home/pradeeban
or just,
$ scp cloudsim-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar cloudsim-examples-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar cloud2sim-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar pradeeban@146.193.41.145:/home/pradeeban
and
$ scp -r conf pradeeban@146.193.41.145:/home/pradeeban/


